Both the World Health Organization and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention have repeatedly said that ordinary citizens do not need to wear masks unless they are sick and coughing.
And as health care workers around the world face shortages of N95 masks and protective gear, public health officials have warned people not to hoard masks.
On Monday during the coronavirus task force briefing, President Trump was asked whether Americans should wear nonmedical masks.
Some people are infected and transmitting the virus probably as long as two days before showing any symptoms, he said.